    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The reason `pipe` modifies your original dataframe in this case, is because the function `rename_levels` that you have written modifies the passed dataframe in place (`df.index = df.index.set_names(..)` will modify the index of `df` in place). \r\nIf you want to avoid this, you could add a `df.copy()` in that function."
